{{Infobox person | name = Dr. Iain McGilchrist | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1953<!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = British | other_names = | known_for = The book ''[[The Master and His Emissary]]'' | occupation = Psychiatrist, writer }} '''Iain McGilchrist''' is a [[psychiatrist]], writer, and former [[University of Oxford|Oxford]] literary scholar.<ref name=neurojournal>{{cite journal | last = Kingerlee | first = Roger |author2=Testa, Rita | authorlink = | title = Review of The Master and his Emissary | journal = Neuropsychoanalysis | volume = 12 | issue = 2 | pages = 222–226 | publisher = Karnac Books for the International Neuropsychoanalysis Society | year = 2011 | url = | doi = }}</ref> McGilchrist came to prominence after the publication of his book ''[[The Master and His Emissary]]'', subtitled ''The Divided Brain and the Making of the Western World''.<ref name="neurojournal"/>
McGilchrist read English at [[New College, Oxford]], but having published ''Against Criticism'' in 1982,<ref name="scimednetCV">{{cite web | last = Staff | first = | title = Scientific and Medical Network Annual Gathering 2009 (pdf) | publisher = The Scientific and Medical Network | year = 2009 | url = http://www.scimednet.org/assets/public/pdf-leaflets/09AGM.pdf | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101216024052/https://www.scimednet.org/assets/public/pdf-leaflets/09AGM.pdf | archive-date = 16 December 2010 | dead-url = yes | accessdate = 2009-12-22}}</ref> he later retrained in [[medicine]] and has been a [[neuroimaging]] researcher at [[Johns Hopkins University]] in Baltimore and a Consultant Psychiatrist at the [[Maudsley Hospital]] in south London.<ref name="scimednetCV" /> McGilchrist is a Fellow of the [[Royal College of Psychiatrists]], and has three times been elected a Fellow of [[All Souls College, Oxford]].<ref name="scimednetCV" />
According to his web site, McGilchrist currently works privately as a consultant psychiatrist in London, and otherwise lives on the [[Skye|Isle of Skye]], off the coast of [[Scotland]].<ref name="LondonSkye">{{cite web | last = McGilchrist | first = Iain | authorlink = | title = About Iain – Iain McGilchrist | publisher = ''iainmcgilchrist.com'' | year = 2009 | url = http://iainmcgilchrist.com/iain/ | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180423132729/http://iainmcgilchrist.com/iain/ | archive-date = 23 April 2018 | dead-url = no | accessdate = 23 April 2018}} From the author's web site 'About' page.</ref>
