'''Louise-Anastasia Serment''' (Grenoble, 1642 - Paris, 1692) was a [[France|French]] [[natural philosopher]] and poet. Born in Grenoble, she spent most of her life in Paris. She was a disciple of [[Descartes]]. She was a member of the [[Ricovrati Academy]]. Serment reputedly collaborated as an author with [[Philippe Quinault]] in his operas.<ref>Jane Stevenson: Women Latin Poets: Language, Gender, and Authority, from Antiquity to the Eighteenth century, 2005</ref>
==References== {{Reflist}} * Renate Strohmeier: ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=-FtSGjEvC8MC&pg=PA253&lpg=PA253&dq=Serment,+Louise-Anastasia+(1642-1692)&source=bl&ots=FwTmhD4tRW&sig=i-Uh0JllXcrpAID66835fD-F2bk&hl=sv&sa=X&ei=OfkwUb3ZNIT-4QTHuIHQDw&ved=0CGkQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=Serment%2C%20Louise-Anastasia%20(1642-1692)&f=false Lexikon der Naturwissenschaftlerinnen und naturkundigen Frauen Europas]'', 1998 * Jane Stevenson: ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=iiMbQDFUfPoC&pg=PA327&lpg=PA327&dq=Louise+Serment++Ricovrati&source=bl&ots=Cw5QmSMRlw&sig=tcaLvjkxn0M2A4B5LkpL51QLnhM&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiFub-3jLLOAhVIDJoKHW0GAqcQ6AEIHTAA#v=onepage&q=Louise%20Serment%20%20Ricovrati&f=false Women Latin Poets: Language, Gender, and Authority, from Antiquity to the Eighteenth century]'', 2005 {{Authority control}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Serment, Louise-Anastasia}} [[Category:1642 births]] [[Category:1692 deaths]] [[Category:17th-century French women writers]] [[Category:17th-century writers]] [[Category:Natural philosophers]] [[Category:French women philosophers]] [[Category:17th-century philosophers]] [[Category:French philosophers]] [[Category:French women poets]] [[Category:17th-century French poets]]
