'''Rousseau on Women, Love, and Family''' is an anthology of works by [[French philosopher]] [[Jean-Jacques Rousseau]] covering five themes: women and politics, gender identity, women, love, and family. The volume was edited by Christopher Kelly and Eve Grace. It includes four passages from Rousseau's ''[[Emile, or On Education|Emile]]'', and excerpts from his ''[[Letter to M. D'Alembert on Spectacles|Letter to d'Alembert]]'', ''Levite of Ephraim'' and [[Emile,_or_On_Education#Émile_et_Sophie|Émile et Sophie]]. Two of the letters to "Henriette" were translated for the first time by the editors for inclusion in this volume.<ref>{{Cite journal| issn = 1468-2931| volume = 64| issue = 1| pages = 87–88| last = Sonenscher| first = Michael| title = Rousseau on Women, Love, and Family (review)| journal = French Studies: A Quarterly Review| accessdate = 2018-07-02| date = 2010-01-09| url = http://muse.jhu.edu/article/369433 |via=[[Project MUSE]] |subscription=yes}}</ref>
